{"title_page": "Ministry of Commerce and Industry (India)", "text_new": "{{use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{use Indian English|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox Government agency\n|agency_name     = Ministry of Commerce and Industry (India)\n|seal            = Emblem_of_India.svg\n|seal_width      = 70\n|seal_caption    = [[Emblem of India]]\n| [[File:The Union Minister for Commerce & Industry, Shri Suresh Prabhakar Prabhu holding a Press Conference on the 3rd meeting of Council for Trade Development and Promotion, in New Delhi on January 08, 2018.jpg|60px]]\n|jurisdiction    = {{flagicon|India}}[[Republic of India]]\n|headquarters    = [[New Delhi]]\n| [[File:The Union Minister for Commerce & Industry, Shri Suresh Prabhakar Prabhu holding a Press Conference on the 3rd meeting of Council for Trade Development and Promotion, in New Delhi on January 08, 2018.jpg|60px]]\n\n|chief1_name     = [[Piyush Goyal]]\n|chief1_position = [[Cabinet Minister]]\n|website        = [http://commerce.gov.in/ Department of Commerce] \n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://commerce.gov.in/#|title=Welcome to department of commerce, Government of India|first=Welcome to department of commerce, Government of|last=India|website=commerce.gov.in}}</ref>\n                  [http://dipp.nic.in/English/default.aspx Department of Industrial Policy and Promotion]\n|logo=|formed=|employees=|budget=|chief2_name=[[Hardeep Singh Puri]]|chief2_position=[[Minister of State]]|chief3_name=[[Som Parkash]]|chief3_position=[[Minister of State]]|chief4_name=|chief4_position=|chief5_name=|chief5_position=|chief6_name=|chief6_position=|chief7_name=|chief7_position=|chief8_name=|chief8_position=|chief9_name=|chief9_position=|parent_department=}}\n\n{{Politics of India}}\nThe '''Ministry of Commerce and Industry''' administers two departments, the Department of Commerce and the Department for Promotion of Industry & Internal Trade (formerly Department of Industrial Policy & Promotion). The head of the Ministry is a Minister of Cabinet rank.\n\n== Minister of Commerce and Industry ==\n{{Infobox political post\n|post            = Minister of Commerce and Industry<br /><small>('' \u0935\u093e\u0923\u093f\u091c\u094d\u092f \u090f\u0935\u0902 \u0909\u0926\u094d\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940'')</small>\n|body            =\n|nativename      =\n|flag            =\n|flagsize        =\n|flagborder      =\n|flagcaption     =\n|insignia        = Emblem of India.svg\n|insigniasize    = 100px\n|insigniacaption = [[Emblem of India]]\n|department      = Ministry of Commerce and Industry\n|style = [[The Honourable]]\n|image           =\n|imagesize       =\n|alt             =\n|incumbent       = [[Piyush Goyal]]<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Minister of State (Independent Charge)</ref>\n|incumbentsince  = 03 September 2017\n|residence       =\n|nominator       = [[Prime Minister of India|Prime Minister]]\n|nominatorpost   =\n|appointer       = [[President of India|President]] <small>(on the advice of the [[Prime Minister of India|Prime Minister]])</small>\n|appointerpost   = \n|termlength      =\n|inaugural       =\n|formation       =\n|last            =\n|abolished       =\n|succession      =\n|deputy          =\n|salary          =\n|website         = {{URL|https://commerce.gov.in/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Minister of Commerce and Industry''' is the head of the Ministry of Commerce and Industry and one of the [[Cabinet minister (India)|cabinet ministers]] of the [[Government of India]]. The first Minister of Commerce and Industry of independent India was [[Syama Prasad Mukherjee]]. The current Minister is [[Piyush Goyal]] of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]. Goyal took over from [[Suresh Prabhu]] on 31 May 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=List of ministers in Narendra Modi's government|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-05-27/news/50122791_1_portfolios-public-grievances-smt|accessdate=28 June 2014|work=[[The Economic Times]]|date=27 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n\n===Past Ministers: Industry===