l]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Janata Dal/meta/color}}\" rowspan=1|\n|rowspan=1| [[H. D. Dewe Gowda]]\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Bolla Bulli Ramaiah]]<br>''(Commerce)''\n| \n| 29 June 1996\n| 19 March 1998\n|| [[Telugu Desam Party]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Telugu Desam Party/meta/color}}\" rowspan=1|\n|rowspan=1| [[H. D. Dewe Gowda]]<br>[[Inder Kumar Gujral]]\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Ramakrishna Hegde]]<br>''(Commerce)''<ref name=rajya>{{cite web |title=Rajya Sabha Members Biographical Sketches 1952 - 2003: H| url = http://rajyasabha.nic.in/rsnew/pre_member/1952_2003/h.pdf | accessdate = 2014-09-01|pages=3\u20134}}</ref><ref>Minister of Commerce</ref>\n| \n| 19 March 1998\n| 13 October 1999\n|| [[Lok Shakti]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Lok Shakti/meta/color}}\" rowspan=1|\n|rowspan=4| [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]]\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Murasoli Maran]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''\n| [[File:Murasoli Maran 2004 stamp of India.jpg|60px]]\n| 13 October 1999\n| 09 November 2002\n|| [[Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam|DMK]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam/meta/color}}\" rowspan=1|\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n|[[Arun Shourie]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''\n| \n| 09 November 2002\n| 29 January 2003\n|rowspan=2| [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Bharatiya Janata Party/meta/color}}\" rowspan=2|\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n|[[Arun Jaitley]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''\n| [[File:Arun Jaitley, Minister.jpg|60px]]\n| 29 January 2003\n| 22 May 2004\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Kamal Nath]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/members/former_Biography.aspx?mpsno=175 |title=Sixteenth Lok Sabha Members Bioprofile : Kamal Nath,Shri |website=loksabha.nic.in |publisher=[[National Informatics Centre]] |accessdate=August 29, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903091049/http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/members/former_Biography.aspx?mpsno=175 |archive-date=3 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> \n| [[File:KamalNath.jpg|60px]]\n| 23 May 2004\n| 22 May 2009\n| rowspan=2| [[Indian National Congress]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Indian National Congress/meta/color}}\" rowspan=2|\n| rowspan=2| [[Manmohan Singh]]\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Anand Sharma]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://164.100.47.5/newmembers/Website/Main.aspx |title=Webpage of Shri Anand Sharma, Member of Parliament (RAJYA SABHA) |date= |website=rajyasabha.nic.in |publisher=[[National Informatics Centre]] |accessdate=August 29, 2014}}</ref> \n| [[File:Anand Sharma - World Economic Forum Annual Meeting 2012.jpg|60px]]\n| 22 May 2009\n| 26 May 2014\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Nirmala Sitharaman]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''<br>''(MoS, Independent Charge)''\n| [[File:Nirmala Sitharaman (cropped).jpg|60px]]\n| 26 May 2014\n| 3 September 2017\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Bharatiya Janata Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Narendra Modi]]\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Suresh Prabhu]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''\n| [[File:The Union Minister for Commerce & Industry, Shri Suresh Prabhakar Prabhu holding a Press Conference on the 3rd meeting of Council for Trade Development and Promotion, in New Delhi on January 08, 2018.jpg|60px]]\n| 3 September 2017\n| 30 May 2019\n|-\n|[[Piyush Goyal]]<br>''(Commerce and Industry)''\n|[[File:Piyush Goyal (cropped).jpg|frameless|80x80px]]\n|31 May 2019\n|Incumbent\n|}\n\n== Department of Commerce ==\nThe department is entrusted with formulating and implementing the [[foreign trade]] policy and responsibilities relating to multilateral and bilateral commercial relations, state trading, [[export]] promotion measures, and development and regulation of certain export oriented industries and commodities.\n\nIn order for the smooth functioning, the Department is divided into eight divisions:<ref>{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.commerce.nic.in/aboutus/aboutus_organisational.asp?id=1\n |title       = Organisational Set-up and Functions\n |publisher   = Department of Commerce, Government of India\n |accessdate  = 2008-11-06\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20081019063202/http://commerce.nic.in/aboutus/aboutus_organisational.asp?id=1\n |archivedate = 19 October 2008\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref>\n* Administrative and General Division[[File:Ministry of Commerce and Industries India.jpg|alt=Ministry of Commerce and Industries India|thumb|Ministry of Commerce and Industries India]]\n* Finance Division\n* Economic Division\n* Trade Policy Division\n* Foreign Trade Territorial Division\n* State Trading & Infrastructure Division\n* Supply Division\n* Plantation Division\n\nThe subjects under the administrative control of the Department include:<ref>{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.commerce.nic.in/aboutus/aboutus_subject.asp?id=2\n |title       = Subjects under Administrative Control\n |publisher   = Department of Commerce, Government of India\n |accessdate  = 2008-11-06\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20081219201038/http://www.commerce.nic.in/aboutus/aboutus_subject.asp?id=2\n |archivedate = 19 December 2008\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref>\n* International trade\n* Foreign Trade\n* State trading\n* Management of Indian Trade Services\n* [[Special Economic Zone]]s\n\n== Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade ==\n{{main article|Department of Industrial Policy & Promotion (India)}}\nThis department was established in the year 1995, and in the year 2000 Department of Industrial Development was merged with it. This department is responsible for formulation and implementation of promotional and developmental measures for growth of the [[industrial sector]], keeping in view the national priorities and socio-economic objectives. While individual administrative ministries look after the production, distribution, development and planning aspects of specific industries allocated to them, Department of Industrial Policy & Promotion is responsible for the overall Industrial Policy. It is also responsible for facilitating and increasing the FDI flows to the country. It is also responsible to calculate WPI (I.e. Wholesale Price Index).\n\nPolicy and Promotion is also responsible for [[intellectual property]] rights relating to [[patent]]s, designs, [[trademark]]s, and geographical indication of goods and oversees the initiative relating to their promotion and protection.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20111201191235/http://commerce.nic.in/ Department of Commerce]\n*[http://dipp.nic.in/ Department of Industrial Policy & Promotion]\n*[https://www.classiciasacademy.com/blog/commerce-ministry-has-unveiled-the-draft-export-policy/ Commerce Ministry Has Unveiled The Draft Export Policy]\n{{Union ministries of India}}\n{{Economy of India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ministry Of Commerce And Industry (India)}}\n[[Category:Government ministries of India|Commerce and Industry]]\n[[Category:Anti-dumping authorities]]\n[[Category:Ministry of Commerce and Industry (India)| ]]\n[[Category:Trade ministries|India]]\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{use Indian English|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox Government agency\n|agency_name     = Ministry of Commerce and Industry (India)\n|seal            = Emblem_of_India.svg\n|seal_width      = 70\n|seal_caption    = [[Emblem of India]]\n| [[File:The Union Minister for Commerce & Industry, Shri Suresh Prabhakar Prabhu holding a Press Conference on the 3rd meeting of Council for Trade Development and Promotion, in New Delhi on January 08, 2018.jpg|60px]]\n|jurisdiction    = {{flagicon|India}}[[Republic of India]]\n|headquarters    = [[New Delhi]]\n| [[File:The Union Minister for Commerce & Industry, Shri Suresh Prabhakar Prabhu holding a Press Conference on the 3rd meeting of Council for Trade Development and Promotion, in New Delhi on January 08, 2018.jpg|60px]]\n\n|chief1_name     = [[Piyush Goyal]]\n|chief1_position = [[Cabinet Minister]]\n|website        = [http://commerce.gov.in/ Department of Commerce] \n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://commerce.gov.in/#|title=Welcome to department of commerce, Government of India|first=Welcome to department of commerce, Government of|last=India|website=commerce.gov.in}}</ref>\n                  [http://dipp.nic.in/English/default.aspx Department of Industrial Policy and Promotion]\n|logo=|formed=|employees=|budget=|chief2_name=[[Hardeep Singh Puri]]|chief2_position=[[Minister of State]]|chief3_name=[[Som Parkash]]|chief3_position=[[Minister of State]]|chief4_name=|chief4_position=|chief5_name=|chief5_position=|chief6_name=|chief6_position=|chief7_name=|chief7_position=|chief8_name=|chief8_position=|chief9_name=|chief9_position=|parent_department=}}\n\n{{Politics of India}}\nThe '''Ministry of Commerce and Industry''' administers two departments, the Department of Commerce and the Department for Promotion of Industry & Internal Trade (formerly Department of Industrial Policy & Promotion). The head of the Ministry is a Minister of Cabinet rank.\n\n== Minister of Commerce and Industry ==\n{{Infobox political post\n|post            = Minister of Commerce and Industry<br /><small>('' \u0935\u093e\u0923\u093f\u091c\u094d\u092f \u090f\u0935\u0902 \u0909\u0926\u094d\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940'')</small>\n|body            =\n|nativename      =\n|flag            =\n|flagsize        =\n|flagborder      =\n|flagcaption     =\n|insignia        = Emblem of India.svg\n|insigniasize    = 100px\n|insigniacaption = [[Emblem of India]]\n|department      = Ministry of Commerce and Industry\n|style = [[The Honourable]]\n|image           =\n|imagesize       =\n|alt             =\n|incumbent       = [[Piyush Goyal]]<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Minister of State (Independent Charge)</ref>\n|incumbentsince  = 03 September 2017\n|residence       =\n|nominator       = [[Prime Minister of India|Prime Minister]]\n|nominatorpost   =\n|appointer       = [[President of India|President]] <small>(on the advice of the [[Prime Minister of India|Prime Minister]])</small>\n|appointerpost   = \n|termlength      =\n|inaugural       =\n|formation       =\n|last            =\n|abolished       =\n|succession      =\n|deputy          =\n|salary          =\n|website         = {{URL|https://commerce.gov.in/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Minister of Commerce and Industry''' is the head of the Ministry of Commerce and Industry and one of the [[Cabinet minister (India)|cabinet ministers]] of the [[Government of India]]. The first Minister of Commerce and Industry of independent India was [[Syama Prasad Mukherjee]]. The current Minister is [[Piyush Goyal]] of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]. Goyal took over from [[Suresh Prabhu]] on 31 May 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=List of ministers in Narendra Modi's government|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-05-27/news/50122791_1_portfolios-public-grievances-smt|accessdate=28 June 2014|work=[[The Economic Times]]|date=27 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n\n===Past Ministers: Industry===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Name\n! Portrait\n! colspan=2|Term of office\n! colspan=2|Party\n! Prime Minister\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Syama Prasad Mukherjee]]\n| [[File:Syama Prasad Mookerjee.jpg|60px]]\n| 15 August 1947\n| 19 April 1950\n| rowspan=11| [[Indian National Congress]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Indian National Congress/meta/color}}\" rowspan=11|\n| rowspan=3| [[Jawaharlal Nehru]]\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Harekrushna Mahtab]]\n|\n| 13 May 1950\n| 26 December 1950\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[Nityanand Kanungo]]\n|\n| 19 July 1963\n| 09 June 1964\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[H. C. Dasappa]]\n|\n| 19 July 1964\n| 29 October 1964\n|rowspan=2| [[Lal Bahadur Shastri]]\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| [[